'''2014年二十国集团布里斯班峰会'''（{{lang-en|2014 G-20 Brisbane summit}}）是[[20国集团|20国集团]][[政府首脑|政府首脑]]第九次会议<ref name="host">[http://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/world-leaders-ask-australia-to-host-next-g20-summit-in-2014/story-fn59niix-1226186429833  "World leaders ask Australia to host next G20 summit in 2014 "] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/world-leaders-ask-australia-to-host-next-g20-summit-in-2014/story-fn59niix-1226186429833 |date=20140911065216 }} [[The_Australian|The Australian]], 5 November 2011</ref>，2014年11月15日-16日于澳大利亚[[昆士兰州|昆士兰州]]首府[[布里斯班|布里斯班]]召开。会场设在[[南布里斯班|南布里斯班]]的[[布里斯本会展中心|布里斯本会展中心]]<ref>{{cite news| title =Brisbane to shunned Sydney: 'Get used to it'| work =| publisher =The Sydney Morning Herald| date =2012-07-11| url =http://www.smh.com.au/opinion/political-news/brisbane-to-shunned-sydney-get-used-to-it-20120710-21tor.html#poll| accessdate =2012-07-06| archive-date =2018-12-25| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20181225090411/https://www.smh.com.au/politics/federal/brisbane-to-shunned-sydney-get-used-to-it-20120710-21tor.html#poll| dead-url =no}}</ref>。

2013年12月1日，布里斯班成为20国集团会议正式举办城市<ref name="btcs">{{Cite news |url=http://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/queensland/brisbane-takes-centre-stage-with-g20-handover-20131130-2yiil.html |title=Brisbane takes centre stage with G20 handover |author=Cameron Atfield |accessdate=2013-12-01 |date=2013-12-01 |work=Brisbane Times |publisher=Fairfax Media |archive-date=2018-12-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225090421/https://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/queensland/brisbane-takes-centre-stage-with-g20-handover-20131130-2yiil.html%20 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2014年11月14日为布里斯班的公众假期<ref>{{cite news| title =Brisbane to get G20 public holiday| work =| publisher =The Courier Mail| date =2013-06-21| url =http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/breaking-news/brisbane-to-get-g20-public-holiday/story-fnihsfrf-1226661166324| accessdate =2013-06-27| archive-date =2018-12-25| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20181225090416/https://www.couriermail.com.au/nocookies?a=A.flavipes| dead-url =no}}</ref>。超过4000名代表和2500名媒体代表出席会议<ref name="pmc">{{cite web |url=http://www.dpmc.gov.au/g20/index.cfm |title=G20 - 2014 |date=2012-12-20 |publisher=Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet |accessdate=2013-01-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130123180413/http://www.dpmc.gov.au/g20/index.cfm |archivedate=2013-01-23 }}</ref>。[[毛里塔尼亚|毛里塔尼亚]]、[[缅甸|缅甸]]、[[新西兰|新西兰]]、[[塞内加尔|塞内加尔]]、[[新加坡|新加坡]]和[[西班牙|西班牙]]的领导人应邀出席本次峰会<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.g20.org/g20_priorities/g20_and_world |title=The G20 and the World |date=2014 |publisher=G20 |accessdate=2014-04-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140211194954/https://www.g20.org/g20_priorities/g20_and_world |archivedate=2014-02-11 }}</ref>。

== 议程 ==

欧洲国家领导人表示，愿意支持经济复苏，协助全球经济摆脱经济危机。[[欧盟委员会|欧盟委员会]]主席[[巴罗佐|巴罗佐]]和[[欧盟理事会|欧盟理事会]]主席[[范龙佩|范龙佩]]强调协调发展战略、敲定金融改革核心协议、税收和反腐败的重要性<ref name="eujl">{{cite web |url=http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_MEMO-14-600_en.htm |title=The EU at the G20 summit in Brisbane: Joint letter of Presidents Barroso and Van Rompuy |date=2014-10-21 |work=Press Release |publisher=European Commission |accessdate=2014-11-11 |archive-date=2014-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141111032141/http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_MEMO-14-600_en.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

Waheguru Pal Singh Sidhu表示，本届峰会的主要目标是“为经济增长、财政再平衡和新兴经济体、投资和基础设施、就业和劳动力流动提供战略重点<ref name="itg20t">{{cite web |url=http://www.eastasiaforum.org/2014/10/02/is-the-g20-the-right-place-to-resolve-the-ukraine-crisis/ |title=Is the G20 the right place to resolve the Ukraine crisis? |author=W. Pal Sidhu |date=2014-11-02 |work=East Asia Forum |publisher=East Asian Bureau of Economic Research |accessdate=2014-11-03 |archive-date=2014-11-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141103073142/http://www.eastasiaforum.org/2014/10/02/is-the-g20-the-right-place-to-resolve-the-ukraine-crisis/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>”。新南威尔士州大学国际金融法教授罗斯·巴克利认为，本次峰会强调的是现有的战略，而非寻求改革协议的措施<ref name="fct">{{Cite news |url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/nov/10/g20-faces-crucial-test-credibility-brisbane-summit-looms |title=G20 faces crucial test of its credibility as Brisbane summit looms |author=Ben Doherty |accessdate=2014-11-11 |date=2014-11-10 |newspaper=The Guardian |publisher=Guardian News and Media |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112024843/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/nov/10/g20-faces-crucial-test-credibility-brisbane-summit-looms |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[气候变化|气候变化]]被排除在本届峰会议题之外，澳大利亚总理[[東尼·艾伯特|東尼·艾伯特]]解释这是为了不让着重于经济增长的议程主体被“搞混”。欧盟和美国的官员对这一突如其来的表示不满<ref>{{cite web|title=<nowiki>EU ‘unhappy’ climate change is off G20 agenda</nowiki>|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/policy/eu-unhappy-climate-change-is-off-g20-agenda/story-e6frg6xf-1226873127864|publisher=The Australian|accessdate=2014-04-07|archive-date=2014-04-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407061512/http://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/policy/eu-unhappy-climate-change-is-off-g20-agenda/story-e6frg6xf-1226873127864|dead-url=no}}</ref>，因为往届峰会都把气候变化列入议事日程<ref name="mcfc">{{Cite news |url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/latest-news/more-calls-for-climate-to-be-added-to-g20/story-fn3dxiwe-1227111047685 |title=More calls for climate to be added to G20 |author=AAP |accessdate=2014-11-03 |date=2014-11-03 |newspaper=The Australian |publisher=News Limited |archive-date=2014-12-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141222092651/http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/latest-news/more-calls-for-climate-to-be-added-to-g20/story-fn3dxiwe-1227111047685 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

当地媒体表示，澳大利亚对议程有显著影响。[[洛伊国际政策研究所|洛伊国际政策研究所]]20国集团研究中心主任表示，20国集团想要获得实质性成果，需将重点放在提高基础设施建设费用、多边贸易体系和打击[[税基侵蚀和利润转移|税基侵蚀和利润转移]]上<ref name="ktis">{{Cite news |url=http://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/queensland/brisbane-g20-summit-key-to-its-success-20131129-2yhds.html |title=Brisbane G20 summit: key to its success |accessdate=2014-05-30 |date=2013-12-01 |work=Brisbane Times |publisher=Fairfax Media |archive-date=2014-05-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140530124336/http://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/queensland/brisbane-g20-summit-key-to-its-success-20131129-2yhds.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。避税问题的讨论，助长了卢森堡与340多家跨国公司间的保密税收协定的披露（参见[[卢森堡避税门|卢森堡避税门]]）<ref>BBC, [http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-29928923 Australia examines global firms' Luxembourg tax deals] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-29928923 |date=20201014015612 }}</ref><ref>Sydney Morning Herald, [http://www.smh.com.au/business/g20/g20-leaders-in-the-mood-to-act-on-tax-avoidance-after-luxembourg-leaks-20141107-11icy3.html G20 leaders in the mood to act on tax avoidance after Luxembourg leaks] {{Wayback|url=http://www.smh.com.au/business/g20/g20-leaders-in-the-mood-to-act-on-tax-avoidance-after-luxembourg-leaks-20141107-11icy3.html |date=20141111025930 }}</ref>。

2014年，二十国集团财长和央行行长多次举行会谈。悉尼在2014年2月21日-23日举办了其中一场<ref>{{cite news| title =Sydney to host G20 finance meeting in 2014| publisher =news.com.au| date =2013-03-20| url =http://www.news.com.au/breaking-news/national/sydney-to-host-g20-finance-meeting-in-2014/story-e6frfku9-1226601451380| accessdate =2013-06-26| archive-date =2019-09-12| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20190912015152/https://www.news.com.au/national/breaking-news/sydney-to-host-g20-finance-meeting-in-2014/news-story/3868ca488c0d175c44b49baaef8e2d4f| dead-url =no}}</ref>，紧接着又于2014年9月在[[凱恩斯_(昆士蘭州)|凯恩斯]]开了一场。9月的会议上，与会各国同意自动交换税务信息以减少[[逃税|逃税]]现象<ref name="g2ca">{{Cite news |url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/sep/21/g20-counties-agree-to-exchange-tax-information-to-stamp-out-evasion |title=G20 countries agree to exchange tax information to stamp out evasion |author=Bridie Jabour |accessdate=2014-09-21 |date=2014-09-21 |work=theguardian.com |publisher=Guardian News and Media |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112024612/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/sep/21/g20-counties-agree-to-exchange-tax-information-to-stamp-out-evasion |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[堪培拉|堪培拉]]举办了二十国集团财长和央行副行长会议<ref>{{cite news| title =Canberra cashes in on G20 meeting| publisher =ABC News| date =2012-09-28| url =http://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-09-28/canberra-to-host-g20-finance-meeting/4285252| accessdate =2013-06-27| archive-date =2013-12-14| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20131214223546/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-09-28/canberra-to-host-g20-finance-meeting/4285252| dead-url =no}}</ref>。2014年7月，二十国集团官方青年活动——二十国集团青年峰会在[[悉尼|悉尼]]举行，而每年的二十国集团劳工和就业部长会议，则于9月在墨尔本举行<ref name="y20a">{{cite web |url=http://y20australia.com/about-y20 |title=About Y20 |date=2013-12-20 |accessdate=2014-07-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714174124/http://y20australia.com/about-y20 |archivedate=2014-07-14 }}</ref>。官方级别的部长级会议全年做开会准备<ref name="2014 Event Schedule">{{cite web|title=2014 Event Schedule|url=https://www.g20.org/australia_2014/event_schedule|website=G20 Australia|publisher=Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet|accessdate=2014-10-30|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141027222323/https://www.g20.org/australia_2014/event_schedule|archivedate=2014-10-27}}</ref>。

== 筹备工作 ==
[[File:G20_Summit_Australia_2014.jpg|right]]
{{Link-en|2011年二十国集团戛纳峰会|2011 G-20 Cannes summit}}期间，时任澳大利亚总理[[朱莉娅·吉拉德|朱莉娅·吉拉德]]提出让澳大利亚举办2014年峰会<ref name="host" />。布里斯本拥有更好的装备以应付显著增加的进港航班，而击败当时[[悉尼会展中心|会展中心]]正在翻修的悉尼<ref name="ggc">{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-07-11/gillards-g20-choice-ruffles-sydneys-feathers/4122900 |title=Gillard's G20 choice ruffles Sydney's feathers |date=2012-07-12 |work=ABC News |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |accessdate=2012-07-12 |archive-date=2012-07-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120712015943/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-07-11/gillards-g20-choice-ruffles-sydneys-feathers/4122900 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2013年10月29日，{{Link-en|昆士兰议会|Parliament of Queensland}}表决通过《二十国集团安保法案》<ref name="qps">{{cite web |url=http://www.police.qld.gov.au/g20/ |title=G20 |publisher=Queensland Police Service |accessdate=2014-05-30 |archive-date=2014-05-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140529113031/http://www.police.qld.gov.au/g20/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

本次活动涉及复杂的安全行动。活动组织者需确保安保措施已经到位，以保护游客，同时要最大限度地减少对内城居民和商家的干扰<ref name="fbf">{{Cite news |url=http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/opinion/editorial-g20-challenge-city-milestone/story-fnihsr9v-1226669001342 |title=G20 challenge city milestone |accessdate=2013-06-26 |date=2013-06-25 |newspaper=The Courier Mail}}</ref>。约6000名昆士兰、乃至全国和新西兰的警方，将确保状况安全<ref name="ilo">{{Cite news |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2014-10-17/independent-legal-observers-to-patrol-brisbane-during-g20-summit/5822950 |title=G20 summit: Independent legal observers to patrol Brisbane in November |author=John Taylor |accessdate=2014-10-17 |date=2014-10-17 |work=ABC News |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |archive-date=2014-10-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141018121506/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2014-10-17/independent-legal-observers-to-patrol-brisbane-during-g20-summit/5822950 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，超过600名志愿者为峰会服务<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.g20.org/community_information/volunteer |title=For Volunteers |author=G20 Taskforce |accessdate=2014-10-19 |date=2014-10-19 |work=G20 Taskforce |publisher=G20 Taskforce |archive-date=2014-10-19 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20141019072906/https://www.g20.org/community_information/volunteer |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

中央商务区和布里斯班机场间的道路被暂时封闭。约1500名安全专家，包括州际和海外人士，与数千名昆士兰州警察，共同执行巡逻任务<ref name="lock">{{Cite news|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/cbd-to-become-fortress-brisbane-for-g20-lockdown-but-ring-of-steel-to-be-as-low-key-as-possible/story-e6frg6n6-1226557074473|title=CBD to become Fortress Brisbane for G20 lockdown, but ring of steel to be as 'low-key' as possible|author=Thomas Chamberlin|accessdate=2013-01-20|date=2013-01-19|newspaper=The Australian (News Limited)|archive-date=2013-01-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130119091254/http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/cbd-to-become-fortress-brisbane-for-g20-lockdown-but-ring-of-steel-to-be-as-low-key-as-possible/story-e6frg6n6-1226557074473|dead-url=no}}</ref>。中央商务区和周边郊区的公共交通服务减少<ref name="">{{cite web |url=http://translink.com.au/travel-information/service-notices/24626/details?utm_source=translink&utm_medium=primary-tile&utm_content=plan-ahead&utm_campaign=public-transport-changes |title=Public transport during the G20 Leader's Summit |date=2014-10-13 |work=Service Notices |publisher=Translink |accessdate=2014-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141021005633/http://translink.com.au/travel-information/service-notices/24626/details?utm_source=translink&utm_medium=primary-tile&utm_content=plan-ahead&utm_campaign=public-transport-changes |archive-date=2014-10-21 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。布里斯班医院的一幢大楼，专门在峰会期间供全球领导人使用<ref name="aoh">{{Cite news |url=http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/queensland/g20-leaders-allocated-own-hospital-wing-for-november-summit-in-brisbane/story-fnihsrf2-1226811588709 |title=G20 leaders allocated own hospital wing for November summit in Brisbane |author=Robyn Ironside |accessdate=2014-05-30 |date=2014-01-28 |newspaper=The Courier-Mail |publisher=News Limited |archive-date=2014-01-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140128032127/http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/queensland/g20-leaders-allocated-own-hospital-wing-for-november-summit-in-brisbane/story-fnihsrf2-1226811588709 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

峰会期间，政府[[无线网络|无线网络]]需要公共安全通信。峰会前，[[Telstra|Telstra]]在[[布里斯班|布里斯班]]、[[黄金海岸_(澳大利亚)|黄金海岸]]和[[凱恩斯_(昆士蘭州)|凯恩斯]]设立网络，随后推广至整个昆士兰州东南部<ref name="qgtb">{{Cite news |url=http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/queensland/queensland-government-to-build-secure-457-million-digital-radio-network-impregnable-to-eavesdroppers/story-fnihsrf2-1226709321633?from=public_rss |title=Queensland Government to build secure $457 million digital radio network impregnable to eavesdroppers |author=Sarah Vogler |accessdate=2013-09-10 |date=2013-09-03 |newspaper=The Courier Mail |publisher=Queensland Newspapers }}</ref>。

澳大利亚政府斥资180万澳元，专为本次峰会租来16辆防弹[[梅赛德斯-奔驰S级|梅赛德斯-奔驰S级]]保镖级别豪华轿车。不过美国总统奥巴马和普京搬来了自己的车<ref name="cars">{{Cite news |url=http://www.news.com.au/national/abbott-government-orders-bombproof-mercedes-to-protect-leaders-at-g20-summit-in-brisbane/story-fncynjr2-1227051984040 |title=Abbott Government orders bombproof Mercedes to protect leaders at G20 Summit in Brisbane |author= |accessdate=2014-10-12 |date=2014-09-09 |publisher=[[News_Corp_Australia|News Corp Australia]] |archive-date=2014-10-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141012111914/http://www.news.com.au/national/abbott-government-orders-bombproof-mercedes-to-protect-leaders-at-g20-summit-in-brisbane/story-fncynjr2-1227051984040 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2014年10月6日，800人参与了应对安全问题、人流管理和交通服务的超过10小时的安全演习。演员们扮成与会代表，搭乘澳航波音737-800客机抵达[[布里斯班国际机场|布里斯班国际机场]]，在由13辆警用摩托车、警车、轿车、面包车、越野车和厢型车的护送下，从机场前往酒店<ref name="secex">{{Cite news |url=http://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/queensland/g20-security-forces-complete-final-major-training-exercise-20141006-10qua3.html |title=G20 security forces complete final major training exercise |author=Kristian Silva |accessdate=2014-10-12 |date=2014-10-06 |publisher=[[Brisbane_Times|Brisbane Times]] |archive-date=2014-10-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141008145942/http://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/queensland/g20-security-forces-complete-final-major-training-exercise-20141006-10qua3.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

