== 安保措施 ==
[[File:Police_boats_on_the_Brisbane_River_November_2014.jpg|thumb]]
11月8日，会场邻近区域被封闭，并由警方把守<ref>Queensland Police G20 Maps list http://www.police.qld.gov.au/G20/maps.htm {{Wayback|url=http://www.police.qld.gov.au/G20/maps.htm |date=20141024182804 }}</ref>。普通公民的自由活动受限。根据《2014年二十国集团安保条例》<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.legislation.qld.gov.au/LEGISLTN/SLS/2014/14SL220.pdf |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2014-11-22 |archive-date=2017-04-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170423051848/https://www.legislation.qld.gov.au/LEGISLTN/SLS/2014/14SL220.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>和《2013年二十国集团安保法》第12条<ref>G20 Bill at legislation QLD {{cite web |url=https://www.legislation.qld.gov.au/LEGISLTN/CURRENT/G/G20SafeSecA13.pdf |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2014-10-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024174348/https://www.legislation.qld.gov.au/LEGISLTN/CURRENT/G/G20SafeSecA13.pdf |archivedate=2014-10-24 }}</ref>，警察专员或部长可随时更改禁区范围。禁区内居民必须接受安检，车辆须配备安全通行证才能通行。<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://news.cctv.com/2016/08/25/ARTI58biXVftz2zqunwcZAwx160825.shtml |title=重要国际会议多国安保之道：整合资源 重点部署_新闻频道_央视网(cctv.com) |accessdate=2021-11-12 |archive-date=2021-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211112054745/http://news.cctv.com/2016/08/25/ARTI58biXVftz2zqunwcZAwx160825.shtml }}</ref>不接受安检的居民，即便缴纳住宿费也会被驱离。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://world.huanqiu.com/article/9CaKrnJFPvb |title=澳布里斯班召开G20峰会 市内封锁店铺关门(图） |accessdate=2021-11-12 |archive-date=2021-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211112054746/https://world.huanqiu.com/article/9CaKrnJFPvb }}</ref>

逮捕令不适用的公民绝对权力不受二十国集团法例限制，除了《2000年警察权利法》所列的无需检控即可拘留、容易触发案件的被捕人士，以及广泛搜查良民<ref>Queensland Police G20 FAQ website http://www.police.qld.gov.au/G20/FAQs.htm {{Wayback|url=http://www.police.qld.gov.au/G20/FAQs.htm |date=20141024182937 }}</ref>、脱衣搜查、禁止在公开场合携带日常家居用品。有后台的官员若不合法遵循指示，将被加重刑罚。《1992年和平集会法案》在峰会期间被暂停，标语牌的大小、允许抗议的内容和地点被严格规范<ref>Lawyers to watch and record Brisbane G20 protests ABC News Website, Oct 17 http://www.abc.net.au/news/2014-10-17/lawyers-set-to-watch-and-record-brisbane-g20-protests/5823438 {{Wayback|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2014-10-17/lawyers-set-to-watch-and-record-brisbane-g20-protests/5823438 |date=20141024124620 }}</ref>。法律观察家在会议期间将监督警力的运行。重罪刑罚将被强制执行，而大多数普通罪行将被判处50-100个单位的罚款，在2014年统一为110元<ref>Queensland Government Sentencing fines and penalties for offences http://www.qld.gov.au/law/crime-and-police/types-of-crime/sentencing-fines-and-penalties-for-offences/ {{Wayback|url=http://www.qld.gov.au/law/crime-and-police/types-of-crime/sentencing-fines-and-penalties-for-offences/ |date=20141024194936 }}</ref>。

